        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Mahila Bakri Palan&amp;quot; was introduced by the Department of Animal Husbandry, Government of Uttarakhand. The scheme aims to empower women, especially abandoned, widowed, destitute, single, and disaster-affected women, by providing them support for goat rearing to generate livelihood and improve household income.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "Under this scheme, one unit of goats (3 females and 1 male) aged 12 to 18 months is provided to eligible women. The entire cost of the scheme, ₹35,000, is borne by the State Government.\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to empower women, especially abandoned, widowed, destitute, single, and disaster-affected women, by providing them support for goat rearing to generate livelihood and improve household income.",
